%N A395939 Decimal expansion of the median distance between two points independently and uniformly selected at random one on each of two opposite faces of a unit cube.
%C A395939 The smallest positive root of the equation (x^2-1)*(3*x^2 - 16*sqrt(x^2-1) + 6*Pi - 3)/6 - 1/2 = 0.
%H A395939 Arak M. Mathai, Peter Moschopoulos, and Giorgio Pederzoli, <a href="https://rivista-statistica.unibo.it/article/view/1104">Distance between random points in a cube</a>, Statistica, Vol. 59, No. 1 (1999), pp. 61-81; <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/268489321">ResearchGate link</a>.
%H A395939 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/CubeLinePickingFaceandFace.html">Cube Line Picking--Face and Face</a>.
%H A395939 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>.
%e A395939 1.123453313472358227814924233437038174965340265016183...
%t A395939 RealDigits[x /. FindRoot[(x^2 - 1)*(3*x^2 - 16*Sqrt[x^2 - 1] + 6*Pi - 3)/6 == 1/2, {x, 1}, WorkingPrecision -> 120]][[1]]
%o A395939 (PARI) solve(x = 1, 1.2, (x^2-1)*(3*x^2 - 16*sqrt(x^2-1) + 6*Pi - 3)/6 - 1/2)
%Y A395939 Cf. A395017, A395937 (mean), A395940 (adjacent faces).
%K A395939 nonn,cons,new
%O A395939 1,3
%A A395939 _Amiram Eldar_, May 11 2026
